{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0652c32ebf243d667ffd3ca2e311b09f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Untested: `--bare --resume <session_id>` together.**\n\n`consultCluster` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:94-99`) always creates a new session — it never passes `resumeSessionId`. So we have no coverage for the combination of bare mode + resume.\n\n### What could go wrong\n\n- `--bare` may create sessions with a different auth state that's incompatible with `--resume`\n- The `.jsonl` format from a bare-created session may not be resume-compatible\n- When Phase 5 (`--fork-session --resume <baseline>`) is added, this incompatibility would silently produce wrong answers rather than errors\n\n### How to detect it\n\nAdd a resume-capable probe using the existing fixture session (`src/claude.ts:124-131`):\n\n```ts\n// In probeProfile — test bare+resume separately from bare alone\nif (profile === \"bare\" && fixtureSessionId) {\n  try {\n    await claude.runPromptWithOptions(\"ping\", {\n      resumeSessionId: fixtureSessionId,\n      extraArgs: [\"--bare\", \"--tools\", \"\"],\n      includeConfiguredExtraArgs: false\n    });\n  } catch (error) {\n    return { available: false, duration_ms: 0, error: `bare+resume failed: ${error.message}` };\n  }\n}\n```\n\nTrack bare+resume as a separate capability. If bare alone works but bare+resume fails, surface the delta before Phase 5 silently uses a broken fork path."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":187,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2946,"cache_read_input_tokens":100826},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e168c3-f7d3-48fb-8e86-0c3c3b4ba74a","uuid":"a1d8eb83-4aa2-4978-8c54-a6cff2d7e093"}
